Yuba River Instream Flow to Habitat Area Relationship

Source: R/data.R
yuba_river_instream.Rd

A dataset containing the Weighted Usable Area (WUA) in square feet per 1000 feet as a function of flow in cubic feet per second

yuba_river_instream

Format

dataframe with 34 rows and 10 variables

flow_cfs

numeric flow value in cubic feet per second

FR_spawn_wua

Fall Run spawning WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

FR_fry

Fall and Spring Run fry WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

FR_juv

Fall and Spring Run juvenile WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

SR_spawn_wua

Spring Run spawning WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

ST_spawn_wua

Steelhead spawning WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

ST_fry_wua

Steelhead fry WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

ST_juv_wua

Steelhead juvenile WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

ST_adult_wua

Steelhead adult WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

watershed

name of watershed
